I have a brand new all-metal Bushmaster XM 15 Optics Ready Carbine with 16" chrome-lined A4-style barrel for sale. Not "brand new with only 100 rounds through it" but totally new. This is a quality factory-built Bushmaster, and not a cheaper DPMS product, or a plastic Carbon 15, or someone's garage build, and a complete ready-to-use package for less than some are selling their used, base model rifle.

It is factory built with the receiver-length picatinny rail, 6-position adjustable stock, A2 flash suppressor on a threaded barrel, bayonet lug, and sling swivels. And unlike most modern AR's, the calibers are stamped on the mag well so you know it accepts BOTH .223 AND 5.56 ammunition, whatever you can find to use - no guessing that the NATO rounds MIGHT go boom without your gun going BOOM!

-A brand new Midway USA padded tactical range bag with 4 velcro pockets to hold 30 round magazines, a middle velcro pocket, and a long zipper pocket.  It has handles and an adjustable strap on the back to carry by hand or over your shoulder.

With this complete AR 15 package you have everything you need, and can get it sighted in on the range and have some fun banging away without having to wait a couple months to find some clean ammo, or pay $1 a round.

The base model MSRP on the rifle is $1,391.48, and with this deal you avoid taxes, fees, and snoopy government agents.  I saw these at the last gun show going for around $1600 without any extras, so I'm listing it at $1500 (with ammo, red dot, wrench, bag, and ammo box included).  I will sell just the rifle, mags, and ammo for $1300.

title: For Sale:  Winchester 1892 Takedown 25-20
postcontent: This feature is hard to find on the '92. The 24 inch octagonal barrel removes in about 10 seconds, and locks up tight again just as fast. Made in the year of our Lord 1911, this rifle was no safe queen. There are light to moderate handing marks on wood and steel, but she is still all there. The action works as designed, including the half cock safety. The bore has considerable shine and less than sharp rifling. It may clean to much better condition. The fairly clear stampings tell me this gun received good care after a day afield. The wood has some added finish, and it looks like some good figure might be hiding under those old layers.
